In this statement, the President expresses concern over recent events in Cuba, such as the death of Orlando Zapata Tamayo, repression against Las Damas de Blanco, and increased harassment of those who speak out for the desires of the Cuban people. The President criticizes Cuban authorities for responding to the aspirations of the people with force instead of embracing change. He joins others in calling for an end to repression, the immediate release of political prisoners, and respect for the basic rights of the Cuban people. The President also mentions his efforts to reach out to the Cuban people and his commitment to supporting their desire for freedom and self-determination.